title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @Willywoo1975
comment: Video gaming at its peak on this Gen console. My only contribution to this great piece of work, would be considering adapting some of the sound effects (gun fire)that made western movies famous in the golden ages of Hollywood. Watching movies made by SERGIO LEONE (Spaghetti Western Producer) would give you a hint of core effects noticeably missing in RDR2. Bar tension scenarios, focused sound effects for specific Characters. What makes movies last forever in some cases are originality in significant material been used to elevate the experience. Recent Star Wars movies suffers from that in the case of the missing original sound of a storm troppers blaster, who in their minds as a sound director does that?. Such mistakes avoided can explain why certain games keep getting remastered, because the replay value are extremely high.

I must say after playing red dead 2 i expected alot better. 

The game is severely clunky, horses hitting trees, trying avoid people in the street, to having to walk in almost every zone when the your playing the game at an intense pace.

 also gameplay and story is really strung out, relies far to heavily on the same ol story mission pattern. Extremely frustrating when it come to a climax but then your left wanting to execute your finish, only to see thw story drag on again.

Huge job to compile all the voice overs and play the story through but it just is not compelling enough to make you feel satisfied.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @DigitalCleaner
comment:
Heads up Mouse and Keyboard users. Controllers have auto aim essentially giving them an aimbot while mouse & keyboard does not. I put in a ticket with Rockstar about this. Here is the response I got:

===============================
Hello,

Thank you for your reply.

We understand your concern regarding the auto-aim not working while using a Keyboard and mouse. We like to inform you that it was as per intended for the keyboard and mouse you can use the controller for the auto-aim. we appreciate your understanding in this regarding.

If you have any other issues please let us know.
Best regards,
Valek N.
Rockstar Support

==============================
Essentially, controller users have a HUGE advantage over you in online mode. They tried to tell me I could turn off "auto aim" to join instances of other users who aren't using them. That was a lie.

Auto aim users can lock onto you through bushes, shrubs, trees and the like and shoot you in the head making online play for keyboard and mouse users completely broken in PVP.

However, I found the single player experience to be triple A and would recommend buying the standard version and just skipping the online.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @michaelw4861
comment:
Even though Red Dead Redemption 2 is an almost perfect game it absolutely doesn't deserve a 10/10 given the terrible controls and some of the worst input lag I have even seen. 
99% of my deaths were because I was either fighting the controls or the controller input lag.
I stopped playing in the hopes Rockstar would eventually fix the issue, but alas they have not. 
Digital Foundry have spoken about it too and they were also surprised it was never fixed. 

Poor controls has always plagued GTA games, but Red Dead 2 is by far the worst.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @JKBlackClover
comment: I’m not exaggerating when I say I’d personally give it a 3. I just had so many problems with the game. The pacing was so painfully slow I wanted to give up multiple times, the realism is just ridiculous how you have to constantly worry about all you bars, it takes forever to loot, and “fast” travel is a joke because 1 you have to manually travel to a place to do it and 2 you can’t do it if you have any bounty. I once travelled for 15 minutes to get to a mission that was literally just a 1 minute cutscene, traveled to a mission that disappeared for no reason, and traveled to one that didn’t let me even do it “due to my recent actions” and it didn’t tell me I couldn’t do the mission until I was already there. I’ve literally seen better controls it decade old games. Dead eye should be unlimited cause that’s the only way you’ll hit anything. On a positive note the characters were extremely well written and there were some amazing story moments. But the story still had some major flaws. It’s super predictable what happens if you played the first game and there is absolutely no reason for it to be 60 hrs long. Ok rant over glad I got that off my chest.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @knightofrose115
comment: This game is one of the best games of all time, but I was a little disappointed by the length of the story. Everyone was saying that the story was going to be roughly 60 hours, but I beat it in 23. I didn't rush through it either, I did a bunch of other side activities such as hunting the legendary fish and catching the legendary fish. I did all the stranger missions when they showed up on the map before I did any story missions. Doing all that plus the story and epilogue only took me 32 hours. I'm not complaining about the game at all, in fact I would put it in my top 3 games. It's just that it all ended so quickly, or at least it felt like it. They could've had you go to Tahiti in the game but somehow you had to go back, or at least you could've explored more of guarma, and maybe they could let you do fishing trips there to catch sharks or huge exotic river fish or something. The game was amazing and I hope the next installment doesn't take as long to make.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @billyrattlesticks6949
comment: Why does this get so much man love?? I've been playing it for weeks and it's terrible. Yes the graphics, story and sound are amazing but the gameplay is some of the worst I've ever come across. The shooting mechanics are awful, you spend most of your time reloading after every 2 shots, there are ZERO decent guns in the game, they all feel as much use as throwing sandbags, you can shoot some guy in the chest at point blank range with a so called powerful rifle and he just keeps on shooting. The health and stamina system with all this cores and health bars for both you and separately for your horse is a nightmare and it feels like I'm constantly farting around with the satchel, trying to keep everything topped up. Your horse is a complete nightmare, it runs head first into trees and knocks you off, it panics when your in battle and bucks you off then runs away, it can jump over a 5 ft fence but then falls over a 3 inch boulder, everything feels slow and awkward, you have to walk like a snail through certain places like camps and there's far to many "follow me at a snails pace" missions, if you take away the admittedly great presentation of the game, it's a poorly executed and dull open world game that's not even close to be the wonderful game people are making it out to be. I seriously wanted to love this game but I'm finding it a real chore to get through :( No doubt the fan boys will attack me in droves for this.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @laithghamyan1901
comment: At first when playing this game, I thought it was mediocre, since you were just doing these boring missions to unlock the weapons that you wanted, for example. But when chapter 4 hit, that is when I really started to understand all the characters and I actually started to care for them (Micah being an exception), but all of them had something that was unique and charming about them. When I started to reach the ending (or the false one) I started to get very sad, as I could not handle experiencing this game and not being able to replay it again since I know what happens. However, the false ending of this game was the saddest and most painful art in any video game I have ever played, and while I did not cry of course, it was like my heart was wrenching and opening up in a way that has not happened in a while. This game is the greatest and most immersive game I have ever played in my life, and it FAR surpasses GTA 5 in my opinion, better than any rockstar game before. I hope that GTA 6 will take lessons from this game and provide a experience that cannot be missed

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @bonkj4285
comment: After spending all this time with it. I will not play another second until rockstar patches the offline replay system. 1 you dont get your gear, your stuck with a lame horse. Im not a hater i enjoy the game, until 1,2, 3 hours go by and im still on certain missions for gold. Thus is massing worldwide as a PROBLEM! Beat it in a week. I try to go back to replay and its not worth the replay. Its NOT WORTH the ONLINE. Rockstar i give a 10/10 for effort. This game didnt last as long as you thought it would for me, and MANY others. I scurry the map for early guns, just to realize when i die (even with the retry from checkpoint  restart) i dont even have them....the replay is why fans are PLAYING! Its not your online, your numbers will support this claim. Restart. Restart. Restart. Restart. Restart. Cant achieve 1 requirement at a time, gotta catch'em all. This isn't pokemon. The controls are what i expected from the last version, but your replay system. Rockstar, you may be callous king, but as a loyal subject, i can tell when your trying to squeeze, drag, or shortcut something. Intentionally or not.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @mickyzzzeee
comment:
I have played the game extremely slowly. Over 100 hours in and just reached chapter 5. The attention to detail, storyline, and the shear scale is quite simply unbelievable. I cannot find a fault in this game other than the fishing mechanics when trying to catch legendary fish, and the shooting mechanics are average...and there are a few frustrating glitches. That being said, definitely one of the games of the decade...
One word of advice when playing...take it slow, don’t rush through the main missions because you will miss a lot of content which is quite frankly just as interesting.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @jamestreveil4866
comment:
I'm not going to say this is the best game ever. I haven't played enough of the games which could be considered to have that crown to say it with any certainty. This is however, without a shadow of a doubt the best game I have ever played. 

 I have never felt as emotionally attached to  a set of characters in a video game before. It made me laugh, it made me cry, it gave me massive adrenaline rushes and also moments of peace and serenity. It made me think and meditate on some issues. But I think most importantly it was just damn fun and very different to a lot of games out there at the moment. I just finished the final epilogue and I feel sad that it's ended.

comment: I'll go out on a limb and say the red dead series is the best game series to ever have been developed, no one even comes close. Emotional, Beautiful, high stakes action and such a deep immersive open world will make you feel like you are literally living your wild west fantasy. I love how Rockstar encourages such massive world building encompassed with such amazing and interwoven storylines. This is what taking time and putting in the effort results in, This series will probably be the best games you will EVER play in your life!!! I can't even imagine what the next one in the series will be like but what I can  do though is mah ghuuurl nagging, "I feel like you are not spending enough time with me like you used to."

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @sebastiangarcia6103
comment:
(Review sin Spoilers*) 9.5/10
Yo ya estoy en el epilogo y se puede decir que la história base ya la complete: el juego en efecto es muy calmado (no significa que  no tenga accion, tiene y buenisima pero eso es una porcion del juego) y el juego me encanto, yo a diferencia de otros jugadores que les parecio aburrido yo acepte el ritmo del juego, las misiones secundarias las disfrute medianamente si senti que los viajes en caballo se sentian largos pero esto era porque el mapa es inmenso. Tu si te esperabas el clasico humor de gta este no lo tiene porque es algo separado a este, aunque si que tiene este clasico sabor a rockstar , si tu hablas con los npc esntenderas porque. 
El mundo es bello y relajante (otros diran aburrido pero bacio jamas) 

En la historia que me parecio exelente y memorable y que creo que dross no ha llegado a ver por no terminarlo ya que al 75% de la historia de Arthur Morgan es muy lento a diferencia del resto que es exquisito.  Mi proboblema con ese 75% es en efecto la banda balla bola de personajes olvidables no los conoces ni sabes porque estan ahi masque para apoyarce entre si esto si que me molesto ya que hasta el mismisimo dutch nunca entendí porque lo veneraban tanto al punto de creer que los personajes eran ignorantes ya hasta el final les empece a agarrar cariño y se logro desarrollar bien el final y te pone en unas hermosas letras mayusculas la palabra REDENCIÓN y entiendes porque el juego lo tiene en el titulo. Este aspecto haciendolo lo mejor y mi parte favorita del modo historia. 

Algo que si me parecio una patada en las bolas es algo que yo llamó realismo extremo que biene siendo esto de que el caballo se canse,  lastime y muera,  el desgaste de armas y tener que cuidar los nucleos del personaje (comer, dormir ) hasta estar rasurandose cada cuanto.  Como me jodia ir hasta no se donde para reabasteserme de municion (porque no todos los pueblos tiene tienes de armas) 

No hace falta que mencione que el online todavia no sale y dado que el online de gta v me es adctivo yo siendo un nivel 450 en este puede que hasta el modo online de RDR sea el 50% del contenido neto del juego

En fin si logras asimilar el ritmo del juego te parecera como ami una de las mejores experiencias de videojuegos en esta generacion de consolas y eso sin contar el proximo modo online 9.5/10

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @mattbonner2518
comment: Meh. More of a cowboy simulator than a video game at times. RDR1 was so laborious that near the end I had simply quit without finishing, and this one looks to have even more "fun" chores. No I don't want to brush my horse, clean my rifle, chop wood, skin animals, or play poker (I'll play poker elsewhere when I want to), I don't care how nice the animations are. That isn't fun. It's as if the game director doesn't do any manual labor in the real world and subconsciously misses it so he mandates it in the virtual world. I barely got through some of the GTA5 boring stuff, and I bet the new GTA will have me mow my lawn as a "side mission" or maybe they'll make a VR game where I actually wash dishes.. Rockstar doesn't learn anything from their previous games, as they just read 10/10 reviews like this one and move on to the next one. But hey let's talk about how beautiful the mountain west is.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review

comment: Great game! My only complaint is how incredibly controlling the programming is, limiting your decision to move the character in the way that you please. To me that is a failure in the gameplay. If the gamer wants to sprint they should let them instead of force them to walk just because they don’t want them to run. Also selecting options is a bit annoying. But everything else is phenomenal. Probably rockstars best game.

I want to like this game so bad I just dont get it.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @jeremywhitmon5670
comment: Originally gave this game a 9/10. Changed it to a 7.5 or an 8 after playing a bit longer. The story and small details are great, but the story is also just a little too slow burning. Just started chapter 4 after spending 30 hours in the game and it has just started to get slightly exciting. The story is the only thing that is keeping me going. Side activities are already boring. Gunfights don't last very long at all and are far too easy. I don't mind the realistic slow paced gunfights, but at least make them challenging and last more that 2 minutes. Don't get me wrong, I have had alot of fun with this game, but it isn't a game changer like people claim it to be. If this game had come out 4 years ago, I probably would have given it a 9.5/10.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @finalmattasy
comment:
Just finished the story. It seems like the quality control went down at RockstarNorth a bit for this. But at the same time things like hardware improvements, the setting, and the music make it an amazing game to play.
Sometimes the game feels like a 10, other times it feels like a 7.5. I think Daniel Lanois' music and snow physics will make this game seem better than it actually is for years to come. =) 
How many Rockstar games have I played with the exact same systems in place... How many trees murdered my horse!? How many swaths of guys did I hide behind a rock to avoid seemingly random gunshots from, and then peekaboo shoot in the head? How many times did I ride my horse listening to high quality npc voice acting, then kill people, over and over and over again..? And still, I wish the dialogue at the end was better than it was.
 The graphics are both blurry and gorgeous. The sound is "best ever" level.
Mountains and Daniel Lanois FTW!

I went from dancing along side Dutch, to singing songs, drinking beers around the campfire, and telling stories with Sean, Uncle, Tammy, and some others. title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @CartelGaming
comment: Having bought and played RDR2 I can 100% say that the game is not a 10/10. I'd probably say it's about a 6/6.5. In general the story is pretty boring, the gameplay is pretty sluggish and is a total aim assist fest, the graphics seem pretty underwhelming but that's probably down to hardware limitations and Rockstar not releasing the game on PC. And lastly the lands are barren and don't have many fun things to do. Overall I think the game is kinda boring and the graphics on console are that bad that I can't even appreciate them. The resolution is definitely under 1080p on a standard xbox/PS4 the fps is probably around 30fps and everything looks very pix elated which completely ruins the immersion.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @TheDuckClock
comment:
Been playing this game since Friday and I'm sorry this is not a 10/10 game. I've had a lot of bugs show up, most of my playtime has been spend traveling from A to B because Rockstar wants to be "realistic" with the fast travel system on the map (seriously why isn't there no way to fast travel TO your camp?

I don't deny that the story is 60 hours long. But the problem is that most of that time has been padding, not to mention the actual missions fall into the same hand-holdy trap as so many previous Rockstar games in the past.

I'm willing to bet that it was given a 10/10 out of fear. Because I've seen the responses from websites that have given the game a 9 or lower (A 9 is still an amazing score) and the reviewers have received death threats from crazy fans. One even had his address dropped online in a scare tactic to make him change his score.

author: @Planted_Jungle_Daddy
comment: I found this game to be terribly frustrating.  The mechanics are not intuitive at all, the weapons selection wheel is cumbersome at best, the storage features are also cumbersome, it takes hours of gameplay just to get to the open map where it doesn't let you even walk fast let alone run... After several hours of gameplay I was so frustrated and entirely sick of having to smash buttons for what should be the simplest of tasks, and at times I was in the middle of a mission wondering what they wanted me to do next because that too is somewhat of a mystery.  This was a huge disappointment after waiting 7 years...  Huge let down by RockStar!

comment: The game looks pretty and a lot of work has gone into graphics and animations and detail, but the game is painfully slow...not just the story (that doesn't bother me), but everything, from the way character walks, loots, aims, the way camera moves -- it's all so painfully slow. I'm still not givig up, but at the moment it feels like a chore to play. I haven't played the first red dead in a long, long time, but I don't remember it  being this slow. GTA 5 is most certainly not this slow and clunky.

So RDR2 is amazing but there is one tiny flaw, as I was playing I saw some one using a electronic fan in their house. I did some research, electrical fans were talked about in 1902 and brought out in 1905 and as you say the game is based in 1899 so I had a look around. I found a number of electric trams and one electric car surprisingly, this means that this game is not remotely accurate. For me this is a very big spoiler as it totally ruins the immersion. Just thought I’d let you now.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @jhock9171
comment: My attitude now that the game has released is even more so than what it was prior to its launch. The hype will kill this game, review scores be damned. The reality I believe is that your typical consumer who will play it (which will be many) will ultimately remark on it being ambitious if not more memorable and immense if not more fun. I feel like most will tire themselves on it in these coming months, and all those years of effort, millions of dollars spent (on advertising alone), and hundreds of overworked employees will be left a forgotten memory in an aftermath of 'meh'. There is no GTAV effect here, but I could've told Business Insider that months ago.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @BenWatson90
comment:
This is delicious torture to me. 
A tragic lovestory has never been able to captivate me like this. Not once. Whenever I think about Brokeback Mountain, not only does it hurt emotionally, but physically it hurts too. My throat constricts, I have trouble breathing and tears which I did not know were there well up. It's like a huge chunk of emotion is surfacing from the pit of my stomach and forcing itself through my throat. Never would I have imagined that a fictional story could bewitch me like this, make me feel such strong emotions.
Beautiful scenery, amazing acting and a heartwrenching plot that has touched millions around the world. The English vocabulary is too limited to express accurately what is going through me right now. It's painful but beautiful and I can't help but deliciously torture myself time and time again when I listen to this song. It's like I feel the pain Enis and Jack felt, the mark of a true masterpiece. 
It makes me think of the people who are going through similar heartbreaks. It's terrible that there is still so much hate towards people who aren't heterosexual. Much love and strength to anyone in a similar position. I look forward to the day that we can all be treated as equals.

title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Review
author: @bryncb
comment:
I can't help but feel like the name Red Dead Redemption 2 does the game an injustice. It's clunky, but also the game deserves more than just coming across as a random sequel. Heck, it's a prequel to RDR rather than a sequel anyway. I would have thought that Red Dead Revolver -> Red Dead Redemption was setting precedent for a more interesting naming scheme whereby only the first two words are maintained.

Why not Red Dead Revenge? Red Dead Retribution? Red Dead Rebellion? Red Dead Revolution? Or back to Red Dead Revolver. Or just call the titles Red Dead going forward. Jesus, anything really. Red Dead Redemption 2 really sounds pretty crap. 

Here's hoping it's the best game of all time though. Otherwise I'll be pissed that I bought a PS4 Pro this month for it and preordered the special edition.
